Nigeria Referees Association President, Otunba Tade Azeez told  National Daily at about the progress of Nigeria in world football.

According football administrator, “The referees did very well and also the impression portrayed by referee in this test going on in Kano show that they have always  being training and that has played out in the cause of the test.”

He added, “Quite a number of them did very well in the test, which shows they are ready at anytime to be called upon.”


“The ultimate goal is for Nigeria Referees to participate in the World Cup, and we are strongly determined to achieving that set goal.”

Azeez was however disappointed that Nigeria had no representative in the Elite A camp but hold hopes that this season might possibly get one..
